---
// Print-ready PDF version
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>PR Review Cheat Sheet | Buoy</title>
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
    <style>
      @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400&display=swap');

      * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

      body {
        font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        font-size: 9px;
        line-height: 1.4;
        color: #1a1a1a;
        background: white;
        padding: 0.35in;
        max-width: 8.5in;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      @media print {
        body { padding: 0.25in; }
        .no-print { display: none !important; }
      }

      .header {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: flex-start;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        padding-bottom: 8px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #F97316;
      }

      .logo { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; color: #F97316; }
      h1 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; text-align: right; }
      .subtitle { font-size: 9px; color: #666; text-align: right; }

      .grid-2 {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 10px;
      }

      .section {
        break-inside: avoid;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      .section-header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 6px;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
        padding-bottom: 4px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
      }

      .section-icon { font-size: 12px; }
      .section-title { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600; }

      .pattern {
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .pattern-title {
        font-size: 9px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 3px;
      }

      .comment-box {
        background: #f8f9fa;
        border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
        border-radius: 4px;
        padding: 6px 8px;
        font-size: 8px;
        color: #333;
        font-style: italic;
      }

      .quick-ref {
        margin-top: 10px;
        break-inside: avoid;
      }

      .quick-ref h2 {
        font-size: 10px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
        padding: 3px 6px;
        background: #fff7ed;
        border-left: 3px solid #F97316;
      }

      .ref-table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        font-size: 8px;
      }

      .ref-table th {
        background: #f8f9fa;
        padding: 4px 6px;
        text-align: left;
        font-weight: 600;
        border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
      }

      .ref-table td {
        padding: 4px 6px;
        border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
      }

      .ref-table td:last-child {
        color: #F97316;
        font-style: italic;
      }

      .tips-row {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 10px;
        margin-top: 10px;
      }

      .tip-box {
        background: #f8f9fa;
        border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 8px;
      }

      .tip-title {
        font-size: 9px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }

      .tip-content {
        font-size: 8px;
        color: #666;
      }

      .cta {
        margin-top: 10px;
        padding: 10px;
        background: #f8f9fa;
        border: 1px solid #F97316;
        border-radius: 6px;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .cta h3 { font-size: 10px; margin-bottom: 3px; }
      .cta p { font-size: 8px; color: #666; margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .cta-link {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 4px 12px;
        background: #F97316;
        color: white;
        font-size: 8px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-decoration: none;
        border-radius: 4px;
      }

      .footer {
        margin-top: 8px;
        padding-top: 6px;
        border-top: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        font-size: 7px;
        color: #999;
      }

      .print-button {
        position: fixed;
        top: 20px;
        right: 20px;
        padding: 12px 24px;
        background: #F97316;
        color: white;
        border: none;
        border-radius: 8px;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 600;
        cursor: pointer;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <button class="print-button no-print" onclick="window.print()">Save as PDF</button>

    <header class="header">
      <div class="logo">Buoy</div>
      <div>
        <h1>PR Review Cheat Sheet</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Copy-paste comments for design consistency</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="grid-2">
      <!-- Colors -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-icon">üé®</span>
          <span class="section-title">Colors</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Hardcoded hex value</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"This looks like a hardcoded color. Can we use a design token instead?"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Close but not exact</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"This color (#3A81F5) is close to our primary (#3B82F6). Intentional, or should we use the token?"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Arbitrary Tailwind</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"Can we use a theme color instead of bg-[#3B82F6]?"</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Spacing -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-icon">üìè</span>
          <span class="section-title">Spacing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Off-scale value</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"This spacing (13px) isn't in our scale. Closest: 12px or 16px. Which fits?"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Magic number</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"What's the reasoning behind 37px? If intentional, can we add a comment?"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Inconsistent spacing</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"This spacing differs from similar components. Should we align for consistency?"</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Typography -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-icon">üî§</span>
          <span class="section-title">Typography</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Hardcoded font size</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"Can we use a typography token here instead of the hardcoded size?"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Custom font-family</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"This declares font-family directly. Can we use our typography system?"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Non-standard weight</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"We use 400, 500, 700 for weights. Reason for 600 here?"</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Components -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <span class="section-icon">üß©</span>
          <span class="section-title">Components</span>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Inline style override</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"This inline style overrides the component. Can we use a prop, or add a variant?"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">!important flag</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"I see !important here. Can we solve the specificity issue differently?"</div>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern">
          <div class="pattern-title">Duplicated pattern</div>
          <div class="comment-box">"This looks like our existing ComponentName. Can we use that instead?"</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="quick-ref">
      <h2>Quick Reference</h2>
      <table class="ref-table">
        <tr><th>Issue</th><th>Question to Ask</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Hardcoded color</td><td>"Can we use a token?"</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Arbitrary spacing</td><td>"What's the closest scale value?"</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Custom font size</td><td>"Do we have a type style for this?"</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Inline styles</td><td>"Can a prop or variant handle this?"</td></tr>
        <tr><td>!important</td><td>"What's causing the specificity issue?"</td></tr>
        <tr><td>New CSS file</td><td>"Can existing utilities cover this?"</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Similar to existing</td><td>"Why not use the existing component?"</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Magic number</td><td>"What's the reasoning? Can we document it?"</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="tips-row">
      <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-title">Polite Version</div>
        <div class="tip-content">"I noticed this uses a hardcoded value. Would you mind checking if there's a token? Happy to help find it!"</div>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-box">
        <div class="tip-title">Direct Version</div>
        <div class="tip-content">"Hardcoded color ‚Äî use --color-primary-500 instead."</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cta">
      <h3>Tired of Manual Review?</h3>
      <p>Buoy does this automatically on every PR.</p>
      <a href="https://buoy.design" class="cta-link">Try Free at buoy.design ‚Üí</a>
    </div>

    <footer class="footer">
      <span>¬© 2026 Buoy. The design system drift detector.</span>
      <span>buoy.design</span>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
